%pyspark
from pyjake.sparkmodule import udf_classifyPm10, udf_classifyPm25

pm = pm.select('location', 'station_code', 'datetime', 'pm10', 'pm25')\
       .withColumn('pm10_grade', udf_classifyPm10('pm10'))\
       .withColumn('pm25_grade', udf_classifyPm10('pm25'))

pm.show()

%pyspark
# pm_am = pm.where('station_code = 534422 or station_code = 534491 or station_code = 534463 or station_code = 534461')

def get_subset(spdf_target, stcode):
    from pyjake.sparkmodule import udf_classifyPm10, udf_classifyPm25
    
    subset = spdf_target.where('station_code = %d' % stcode)\
                        .select('datetime', 'pm10', 'pm25')
    subset = subset.withColumn('pm10grade_%d' % stcode, udf_classifyPm10('pm10'))\
                   .withColumn('pm25grade_%d' % stcode, udf_classifyPm10('pm25'))\
                   .withColumnRenamed('pm10', 'pm10_%d' % stcode)\
                   .withColumnRenamed('pm25', 'pm25_%d' % stcode)\
                   .withColumnRenamed('datetime', 'datehour')
    return subset
    

pm1 = get_subset(pm, 534422)
pm2 = get_subset(pm, 534491)
pm3 = get_subset(pm, 534463)
pm4 = get_subset(pm, 534461)

pm1.printSchema()
pm1.show()

%pyspark
pdf_pm1 = pm1.toPandas()
pdf_pm2 = pm2.toPandas()
pdf_pm3 = pm3.toPandas()
pdf_pm4 = pm4.toPandas()

print(pdf_pm1['pm10grade_534422'].value_counts(sort=False))
print(pdf_pm2['pm10grade_534491'].value_counts(sort=False))
print(pdf_pm3['pm10grade_534463'].value_counts(sort=False))
print(pdf_pm4['pm10grade_534461'].value_counts(sort=False))
